                            <comment id="12926495" author="thejas" created="Sat, 30 Oct 2010 00:14:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With this fix, pig does not merge the foreach statements if first foreach has a user defined schema. We should consider supporting that case as well (in a separate jira), because users sometimes add a foreach statement just to give convenient names for columns . &lt;br/&gt;
eg- &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
J = join A by col1, B by col1
F1 = foreach J generate A::col1 as Acol1 , A::col2 as col2, B::col1 as Bcol1; -- foreach that has been added just to give convenient names &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; expressions.
F2 = foreach F1 generate Acol1+col2, Bcol1 + col2 ;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12927038" author="daijy" created="Mon, 1 Nov 2010 16:46:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to both trunk and 0.8 branch. Future improvement is possible as per Thejas&apos;s comment. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
